39:  * href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms679360(v=vs.85).aspx">GetLastError()</a>
40:  * mechanism.<br>
41:  * Some C functions declare errors by marking an error code in <a
42:  * href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Errno.h">errno</a> or through <a
43:  * href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms680627(v=vs.85).aspx">SetLastError(int)</a>.<br>
44:  * If you want their corresponding bindings to throw an exception whenever such
45:  * an error was marked, simply make them throw this exception explicitly.<br>
46:  * On Windows, BridJ will first check <a
47:  * href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms679360(v=vs.85).aspx">GetLastError()</a>,
48:  * then if no error was found it will check <a
49:  * href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Errno.h">errno</a> (on the other platforms
50:  * only <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Errno.h">errno</a> is
